cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.AL

This paper deals with a fundamental problem in wireless networks, specifically in scheduling communication links to minimize interference. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves designing algorithms and conducting complexity analysis, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AL (Algorithms). The problem of scheduling links can also be seen as a distributed computing problem, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of power control, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Signal Processing).
